			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About Revinate</strong><br />
Backed by top tier venture firms (Benchmark Capital and Formation 8) and headquartered in the Presidio of San Francisco at the Letterman Digital Arts Center, Revinate (<a href="http://www.revinate.com">http://www.revinate.com</a>) develops innovative solutions for the world&#39;s leading hotels. Social media has changed the game for hoteliers. Slick ads no longer fill rooms. Guests now use TripAdvisor and Yelp for recommendations, and tap their networks on Facebook and Twitter. Comment cards on nightstands are nice, but public, online feedback is much richer.</p>
<p>
This new world presents serious challenges, and major opportunities, for hotels across the globe. Revinate is the leading provider of social media solutions for hotels, and we&#39;re just getting started. We&#39;ve got a great, experienced team. Our historic offices are in San Francisco&#39;s Presidio, surrounded by a national park. We offer competitive salaries, stock options and rich benefits, and we value our challenging, fun and balanced culture. We&#39;ve been featured in the New York Times, Wall Street Journal, NBC News and many other publications. We&#39;re growing quickly and our customers include many of the world&#39;s leading hotels.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Position</strong><br />
Revinate is looking for a Front End Engineer who is passionate about creating and building beautiful and intuitive web-based social products across a variety of different platforms, and can produce elegant front-end code.</p>
<p>
A successful candidate will build out solid front-end code as well as working with product, engineering and design teams to ensure that users have a quality experience. Our highly efficient and collaborative team uses an agile development methodology so we develop and iterate quickly - it&rsquo;s more important to get features in front of users for feedback than it is to try and define the perfect specification from the start. You should also be passionate about social media, have ideas about how the hospitality industry can best leverage various social media technologies, and also have a strong eye for visual design.</p>
<p>
We&#39;re a small team and this is a chance to work in a highly productive environnent. You&#39;ll not only build out front-end features, but drive design and product decisions, and define features from the ground up.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Create functional mockups from wireframes and product specifications</li>
<li>
Design, specify and help drive the development of new features &amp; enhancements</li>
<li>
Assist in the creation of&nbsp;new features and enhancements from conception to launch</li>
<li>
Be proactive in improving the product as well as our development processes</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Expert in browser standards and cross-browser design</li>
<li>
Expert in producing clear, concise, and correct markup, as well as corresponding styling</li>
<li>
Experience with social media products</li>
<li>
Passionate about social media and staying abreast of current trends</li>
<li>
Ability to work independently and with small teams</li>
<li>
Excellent written and oral communication skills</li>
<li>
Excellent visual design</li>
<li>
Obsession with user interaction and user experience<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Additional Considerations</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience with Javascript and the jQuery/jQuery UI frameworks</li>
<li>
Experience with PHP</li>
<li>
Experience with git<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
This is a full-time job located at our San Francisco headquarters, though for exceptional people we will consider remote candidates. To apply, please submit your resume along with a cover letter explaining why you are ideal for this role, and please include links to your portfolio.</p>
