			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About Revinate</strong></p>
<p>
Revinate is an innovative, fast-growing company and we are the leading provider of social media solutions for the hospitality industry. We process millions of online reviews and social media mentions daily, storing, analyzing and serving up terabytes of data to our globally diverse client base. We offer competitive salaries, stock options, and rich benefits, and we value our challenging, fun, and balanced culture.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Position</strong></p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for software engineers to focus on the development of information retrieval systems using distributed computing and large-scale system design. This will be specifically for spider and ETL technology for aggregating and processing data from social media sites, review sites, and internal data sources. The software engineers should be experienced in distributed systems and building scalable and reliable backend services. Our platform processes tens of millions of pieces of content daily and must be highly performant and resilient to failure, and also scale with our rapid growth. We use an agile development methodology, develop quickly and iteratively, and produce very high quality software. We look for engineers with a passion for solving complex problems and pushing technology to the next level.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Optimize and improve existing spider technology for speed, efficiency, and quality.</li>
<li>
Build highly modular and distributed applications</li>
<li>
Be able to prototype quickly and also develop large-scale robust solutions for production</li>
<li>
Able to quickly and accurately analyze web and internal data sources for extracting all relevant data to configure tools and write scripts for specific crawl jobs</li>
<li>
Profile application code to identify bottlenecks and inefficient algorithms, heuristics, and data queries</li>
<li>
Optimize application caching, cache invalidation, and data querying strategies</li>
<li>
Analyze data models and their relationships to identify inefficiencies</li>
<li>
Ensure graceful degradation of the application in the event of systems failures</li>
<li>
Identify systems more prone to failure and identify suitable replacement or develop solutions to improve fault tolerance and resiliency</li>
<li>
Rapidly troubleshoot and fix bugs and problems</li>
<li>
Be proactive in improving the product as well as development processes</li>
<li>
Design, implement and maintain RESTful backend services</li>
<li>
Refactor and improve the maintainability of the codebase</li>
<li>
Participate in design and code reviews</li>
<li>
Work with our Operations team to implement proper capacity planning procedures</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
B.S. or higher in Degree educated in a relevant technical subject, such as Computer</li>
<li>
Science, Physics, Mathematics or Engineering</li>
<li>
3+ years of relevant work experience in software development</li>
<li>
Experience developing scalable, highly-performant web applications</li>
<li>
Superior Java developer</li>
<li>
Working knowledge of Linux</li>
<li>
Consolidated knowledge of software design patterns</li>
<li>
Excellent (English) written and verbal communication skills</li>
<li>
Self-motivated, loves a challenge, and desire to work in a young dynamic company</li>
<li>
Understanding of networks and distributed computing</li>
<li>
Knowledge of at least one scripting language</li>
<li>
Advanced knowledge of web technologies i.e. REST, JSON, HTTP, DOM HTML, Javascript</li>
<li>
Advanced knowledge of SQL and Databases</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Desired Skills</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Willingness to work in an agile development environment</li>
<li>
Experience with some of the following: PHP, Ruby/Rails. Groovy/Grails, Python</li>
<li>
Familiarity with unit test and automated testing frameworks</li>
<li>
Experience with performance tuning and optimization</li>
<li>
Affinity for open source projects and preferably a regular committer</li>
<li>
Proficiency with git</li>
<li>
Familiarity with NoSQL and related data stores i.e. MongoDB</li>
<li>
Experience with Elastic Search</li>
<li>
Constantly learning new platforms, tools, and frameworks</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>To Apply</strong></p>
<p>
This is a full-time job located at our Munich office in Germany. To apply, please submit your resume along with a cover letter explaining why you are ideal for this role, and please include links to your portfolio.</p>
