<strong>About Revinate</strong></p>
<p>
Headquartered in the Presidio of San Francisco at the Letterman Digital Arts Center, Revinate (http://www.revinate.com ) develops innovative solutions for the world&#39;s leading hotels. We&rsquo;re the leading provider of social media solutions for hotels, with a great, experienced team. We offer competitive salaries, stock options and rich benefits, and we value our challenging, fun and balanced culture. We&#39;ve been featured in the New York Times, Wall Street Journal, NBC News and many other publications. We&#39;re growing quickly and our customers include many of the world&#39;s leading hotels.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Position</strong></p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for an experienced GL accountant to handle monthly closings, posting entries to our accounting system (Quickbooks), reconciling balance sheet accounts, generating monthly financial statements, and analyzing financial performance, with opportunities for advancement. The ideal candidate will have significant accounting experience, be detail oriented, trustworthy and reliable, and able to take responsibility for producing accurate, timely financial statements.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll need to be very collaborative, have very strong communication skills and be passionate about the mission of our company.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Post entries for G/L, reconcile accounts, and prepare monthly financial statements.<br />
&bull; Handle A/R and A/P processes.<br />
&bull; Assist in the budgeting process, and analyze variances to monthly budgets.<br />
&bull; Assist with processing a high volume of monthly invoices using an automated system.<br />
&bull; Contact customers to collect outstanding bills.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; BA degree in accounting or finance, or equivalent experience.<br />
&bull; 6+ years of accounting experience, including preparation of financial statements.<br />
&bull; Experience working for SaaS companies.<br />
&bull; Experience using Quickbooks and Salesforce.com.<br />
&bull; Advanced Excel skills, strong analytical skills and exceptional attention to detail.<br />
&bull; Excellent communication skills and a passion for collaborating with colleagues in all departments.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>To Apply</strong></p>
<p>
Please submit your resume along with a cover letter explaining why you are the right candidate for this role. (Principals only, no recruiters please.)</p>
